(321, 'La leyenda del Ñandu', 'Nelvy Bustamante, Marta Prada', 'Editorial desconocida', '9789500729741', '2008', 'Based on a myth of the (Tehuelche) people about the origin of the Earth. The culture hero Elal faces the wrath of his father, Noshtex, who is envious of his son\'s special powers and wants to kill him. To save the boy, the animals take him to the distant land of Patagonia, the homeland of his descendants today. Includes activities, information about the region and the animals who live there, with a special section on the Rhea bird.', 'Infantiles', 1, 1, 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/21bixJO3RkL._AC_UF1000,1000_QL80_.jpg'),
